column6:
A payment - the logical consequence of a commitment - is the act which discharges Parliament from its obligations to its creditors.
Payments are normally made in settlement of an invoice or in response to a third-party request for payment.Several different actors are involved in the handling of payments:
- the official responsible for initiation creates the transaction;
- the dossier then passes to the ex ante verifier, who carries out an ex ante check;
- the Authorising Officer then signs the transaction validating the expenditure and charges the Accounting Officer with effecting the payment by sending him the payment order.

