column6:
The Technology Scouting capability is the ability to continuously scout outside of the EP, for new and emerging technology by monitoring media and specialised press; by participating in exhibitions and conferences; and by meeting the IT leading companies, including start-ups. The goal of technology scouting is to look ahead to identify new technologies that could be used to address existing and future needs of the EP in an innovative way.  
 
At the EP, six specific areas for technology scouting  have been identified, which the Innovation service constantly monitor as follows:
 * Mobility;
 * Location based services;
 * The internet of things;
 * Data analytics;
 * Collaboration and Communication;
 * Hardware, Apps and tools.

column2:
The Monitoring & Reporting capability is the ability of the organisation to monitor and report on the achievement of its objectives, both at strategic and operational level.
 
The monitoring of corporate activities is based on the use of indicators meant to:
   -  ensure accountability in the use of public funds;
   -  identify the level of attainment of operational objectives;
   -  identify the level of attainment of strategic goals;
   -  identify areas of improvement;
   -  highlight the principles and direction of effort. 
 
Expected outputs - List of Metrics; List of KPIs, Reports (Mid-term/intermediate corporate reports, Annual Reports, strategic reports).

