column4:
Has the objective of protecting computer systems from damage to their hardware, software or electronic data, as well as from disruption or misdirection of the services they provide and is the application of Information Security objectives to the processing of information through Information and Communication Technologies (ICT).  It encompasses the processes, human resources, software and hardware means (known as Information Systems), aiming at maintaining information confidentiality, integrity and availability against intentional or accidental threats, through the implementation of protection, detection and reaction measures proportionate to the level of risk. 
 
Includes Information security:Information security has the following principal objectives:
a.         To guarantee that information, regardless of the medium that holds it, is always available for authorised needs and protected from unauthorised accesses and alterations;
b.         To safeguard European Parliament premises housing information from theft, tampering with, malicious wilful damage and all other unlawful forms of processing;
c.         In the event of a failure or a breach, to assess the damage caused, limit its consequences, identify the perpetrators and adopt the necessary remediation measures without delay, including appropriate judicial actions if deemed necessary.

